			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><b>By Paul Berger.</b><br />
Read by Stephen Eley.
First appeared in <a href="http://www.ideomancer.com/">Ideomancer</a>, December 2004.</p>

<p><i>One must show the proper respect for knowledge, and learn by watching and
counting and copying.  The Doctor does almost nothing but learn &#8211;
although he watches the wrong things &#8212; and some of us think he might be
a little sacred as well, which is one of the reasons he is still alive. 
It might be unlucky to eat a sacred person.</i></p>

<p><i>But the main reason he is still among us is someday we will learn
something valuable from him, and then maybe the village will support the
lives of a few more of the People.  We watch him carefully.</i></p>

<p><b>Rated PG</b>.  Contains mild language, some violence, and the Observer Effect gone very awry.</p>

